1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:30,001
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,045 --> 00:00:40,575
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,575 --> 00:00:41,875
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:01:28,595 --> 00:01:30,425
(Episode 3)

5
00:01:42,805 --> 00:01:43,805
Who...

6
00:01:44,975 --> 00:01:47,075
am I? What's your name?

7
00:01:57,225 --> 00:01:58,425
A mirror.

8
00:02:01,425 --> 00:02:04,325
It hurts...

9
00:02:15,845 --> 00:02:16,845
What are you doing?

10
00:02:22,245 --> 00:02:23,245
You're beautiful.

11
00:02:31,455 --> 00:02:32,695
I'll make sure you never get old.

12
00:02:34,625 --> 00:02:37,465
- You'd hate to get wrinkles?
- Wrinkles of the heart.

13
00:02:39,135 --> 00:02:40,665
I don't care about wrinkles on your face.

14
00:03:28,345 --> 00:03:29,345
Tell me.

15
00:03:30,345 --> 00:03:31,345
Your name.

16
00:03:36,355 --> 00:03:37,855
What am I supposed to say?

17
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:45,465
It hurts...

18
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:47,935
Does it hurt?

19
00:03:53,205 --> 00:03:54,605
You...

20
00:03:55,405 --> 00:03:56,705
want to...

21
00:03:57,545 --> 00:03:58,675
die?

22
00:04:04,215 --> 00:04:05,485
Don't cry.

23
00:04:09,085 --> 00:04:10,955
You succeeded,
and that's all that matters.

24
00:04:11,955 --> 00:04:12,955
You did it.

25
00:04:14,025 --> 00:04:15,255
You worked so hard.

26
00:05:02,005 --> 00:05:03,105
Goodbye.

27
00:05:20,925 --> 00:05:22,025
This is how I live.

28
00:05:28,465 --> 00:05:30,165
I should've brought some fruit.

29
00:05:32,335 --> 00:05:34,705
- I have milk.
- How's Momo?

30
00:05:36,005 --> 00:05:37,575
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

31
00:05:40,975 --> 00:05:43,015
I'm sure she's recovering well.

32
00:05:43,615 --> 00:05:45,315
James said he hasn't heard
anything either.

33
00:05:45,755 --> 00:05:46,755
It's weird, isn't it?

34
00:05:47,015 --> 00:05:48,815
- Why don't you text her?
- You think I haven't?

35
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,395
But you can go see her.

36
00:05:52,455 --> 00:05:55,225
What? How can I just show up
when she hasn't asked me to?

37
00:05:55,865 --> 00:05:59,235
- She's at Dr. Shin's getting treated.
- For seven months?

38
00:06:00,635 --> 00:06:02,465
Then just how serious is it?

39
00:06:04,205 --> 00:06:06,705
Was she completely unconscious
at the time of the accident?

40
00:06:08,205 --> 00:06:11,775
No one at her agency is talking.
They just say she's recovering.

41
00:06:13,615 --> 00:06:14,845
Is that why you're here?

42
00:06:18,815 --> 00:06:21,755
If her condition were bad,
Director Shin would've fallen apart.

43
00:06:22,085 --> 00:06:25,795
Ms. Hyun also had a couple of fittings
and seemed perfectly normal.

44
00:06:30,495 --> 00:06:31,495
Are you leaving?

45
00:06:39,375 --> 00:06:40,375
Hey.

46
00:06:42,345 --> 00:06:43,705
Don't you have anything to say to me?

47
00:06:46,515 --> 00:06:47,515
About what?

48
00:06:48,615 --> 00:06:49,615
You don't know?

49
00:06:52,615 --> 00:06:54,015
It's just that...

50
00:06:54,855 --> 00:06:58,525
I was hurt because I felt like
you started pulling away from me.

51
00:06:59,595 --> 00:07:00,755
You were hurt?

52
00:07:01,025 --> 00:07:02,025
Yes.

53
00:08:27,915 --> 00:08:31,215
For dinner, I want French Toast
and a Caprese Salad.

54
00:08:32,885 --> 00:08:33,885
Okay?

55
00:08:36,785 --> 00:08:39,595
Caprese Salad.

56
00:08:40,255 --> 00:08:42,195
French Toast.

57
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:57,645
Get lost...

58
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:01,375
Get lost.

59
00:09:06,185 --> 00:09:07,385
Get lost.

60
00:09:10,555 --> 00:09:13,095
Is Director Shin still coming
on Wednesday as planned?

61
00:09:40,615 --> 00:09:42,155
There are barely any wrinkles.

62
00:09:43,055 --> 00:09:44,385
I'll look great as long as I dress well.

63
00:09:47,425 --> 00:09:48,425
There.

64
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:57,135
No.

65
00:10:01,035 --> 00:10:03,945
Excellent. Even I have to admit, I look...

66
00:10:04,305 --> 00:10:06,645
mid-thirties?

67
00:10:08,315 --> 00:10:10,185
When is your birthday, Mr. Ha?

68
00:10:10,585 --> 00:10:13,315
I asked Manager Yoon,
but she wouldn't tell me.

69
00:10:13,485 --> 00:10:17,025
I don't take cakes from my employees.
That's too much sugar.

70
00:10:17,085 --> 00:10:19,225
But still, for us...

71
00:10:22,795 --> 00:10:24,365
Jin Ju, do you drink?

72
00:10:24,795 --> 00:10:25,995
A little.

73
00:10:27,295 --> 00:10:28,795
Should we do the wine pairing?
It's been a while.

74
00:10:30,335 --> 00:10:32,805
Natasha's airport look was great today.

75
00:10:33,375 --> 00:10:35,075
I learned from the best.

76
00:10:35,335 --> 00:10:38,605
I can't take all the credit.
You have to have a natural gift for it.

77
00:10:39,675 --> 00:10:43,015
Should I call you Mr. Ha?
Or do you prefer "Sir?"

78
00:10:43,085 --> 00:10:44,445
Call me whatever you want.

79
00:10:45,145 --> 00:10:48,385
To be honest,
neither of those really suit you.

80
00:10:48,755 --> 00:10:50,855
Then what, you want to call me honey?

81
00:10:51,255 --> 00:10:53,895
- You're like a celebrity.
- I'll take that as a compliment.

82
00:10:54,095 --> 00:10:56,095
Of course. I mean it.

83
00:10:59,565 --> 00:11:01,235
This is so delicious.

84
00:11:04,335 --> 00:11:06,235
This is so delicious, Yong Joong.

85
00:11:10,845 --> 00:11:12,375
They have good pairings here.

86
00:11:13,075 --> 00:11:15,275
Is that birthday on your ID your real one?

87
00:11:18,685 --> 00:11:19,685
You don't know?

88
00:11:22,385 --> 00:11:23,385
No.

89
00:11:23,855 --> 00:11:26,455
- What about Reporter Geum Ba Ra?
- It's the same for Ba Ra.

90
00:11:27,295 --> 00:11:29,625
We even entered the orphanage
on the same day.

91
00:11:31,625 --> 00:11:32,635
Really?

92
00:11:33,795 --> 00:11:35,965
You'll just have to find
yourselves good husbands.

93
00:11:37,365 --> 00:11:40,375
- You think that's possible?
- Where there's a will, there's a way.

94
00:11:40,935 --> 00:11:43,505
They say the deity grants at least one
of your most earnest wishes.

95
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:45,875
Then why are you still single?

96
00:11:46,675 --> 00:11:48,175
Because I was too busy
taking care of my young brother.

97
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:51,815
Mr. Ha Yong Joong.
He's ridiculously handsome.

98
00:11:53,615 --> 00:11:55,815
Though he's not quite as handsome
as Director Shin Ju Shin.

99
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:57,755
You clearly don't have an eye for men.

100
00:11:58,385 --> 00:12:01,125
Whether it's looks or anything else,
Yong Joong is way better.

101
00:12:01,525 --> 00:12:04,165
To each their own, I guess.

102
00:12:05,065 --> 00:12:09,605
But Mr. Ha didn't get far academically,
did he?

103
00:12:10,005 --> 00:12:13,175
What does a formal education matter?
It's his character that's important.

104
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:16,745
Besides, Yong Joong is smarter
than people with PhDs.

105
00:12:16,745 --> 00:12:18,345
He reads a lot.

106
00:12:20,145 --> 00:12:21,545
It's so tender.

107
00:12:22,445 --> 00:12:23,615
I'll take you out more often.

108
00:12:25,115 --> 00:12:27,355
Is Reporter Geum Ba Ra seeing anyone?

109
00:12:28,385 --> 00:12:30,525
- I have no idea.
- How could you not know?

110
00:12:30,585 --> 00:12:32,285
You said you're practically sisters.

111
00:12:32,895 --> 00:12:34,525
I get the feeling
she's not interested in marriage.

112
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:37,265
The ones who say they're not interested
in marriage are always the first to marry.

113
00:12:39,365 --> 00:12:40,935
What's Ba Ra's ideal type?

114
00:12:42,395 --> 00:12:43,965
Are you thinking of
setting her up with someone?

115
00:12:46,675 --> 00:12:48,205
You're not thinking of Mr. Ha, are you?

116
00:12:48,475 --> 00:12:49,975
Of course not.

117
00:12:52,405 --> 00:12:53,975
Get lost.

118
00:12:57,215 --> 00:12:59,115
I can't stand the sight of you.

119
00:13:02,155 --> 00:13:04,355
I said, get lost!

120
00:13:06,495 --> 00:13:08,355
Who the heck are you?

121
00:13:09,025 --> 00:13:12,065
Momo, come on. Let Mommy get some sleep.

122
00:13:13,535 --> 00:13:16,335
You're dead meat.

123
00:13:44,965 --> 00:13:46,265
Coffee, and make it weak.

124
00:13:55,235 --> 00:13:56,305
(Post)

125
00:13:59,305 --> 00:14:00,315
What's this?

126
00:14:00,645 --> 00:14:03,245
She's pretty, right?
I thought she might be your type.

127
00:14:04,245 --> 00:14:05,845
(Post)

128
00:14:06,515 --> 00:14:07,755
Looks like she's had work done.

129
00:14:08,815 --> 00:14:12,995
- Nearly everyone gets work done now.
- But you haven't. You're all natural.

130
00:14:14,025 --> 00:14:16,525
- That's because I'm broke.
- You want some?

131
00:14:17,925 --> 00:14:19,495
No, you're perfect just the way you are.

132
00:14:19,795 --> 00:14:20,995
It's not because
I won't give you the money.

133
00:14:22,935 --> 00:14:25,305
"Perfect..."
Is that the right word for a face?

134
00:14:25,905 --> 00:14:27,675
It's more than just being pretty.

135
00:14:28,605 --> 00:14:29,805
Only in your eyes.

136
00:14:31,805 --> 00:14:32,845
She said she's interested in me?

137
00:14:34,775 --> 00:14:38,845
- Yes.
- A PhD likes a middle school dropout?

138
00:14:40,555 --> 00:14:42,515
A high school dropout, to be exact.

139
00:14:42,885 --> 00:14:45,355
- Just meet her once.
- Do you think we'd be a good match?

140
00:14:46,355 --> 00:14:47,355
Yes.

141
00:14:48,455 --> 00:14:50,965
Personality-wise? Our backgrounds?

142
00:14:52,195 --> 00:14:54,995
- She asked me to set you two up.
- I was just asking.

143
00:14:55,065 --> 00:14:56,405
No, you weren't.

144
00:14:57,635 --> 00:14:58,905
You're going to get married, right?

145
00:14:59,575 --> 00:15:01,435
Yes, of course I am.

146
00:15:04,675 --> 00:15:06,975
She comes from a good family,
and she has a great personality.

147
00:15:07,375 --> 00:15:09,045
Plus, she has that foxy look guys go for.

148
00:15:11,715 --> 00:15:13,085
What kind of look do you have, Ba Ra?

149
00:15:18,225 --> 00:15:20,025
I'm clueless
when it comes to women's looks.

150
00:15:21,655 --> 00:15:23,565
Is gaming all you know about?

151
00:15:24,195 --> 00:15:25,225
Pretty much.

152
00:15:28,495 --> 00:15:31,765
Of all the men I know,
aside from our Advisor,

153
00:15:31,835 --> 00:15:33,735
no one is as savvy as you.

154
00:15:33,735 --> 00:15:36,675
You're filled with mature knowledge.

155
00:15:37,875 --> 00:15:39,445
I'll take that as the highest compliment.

156
00:15:39,815 --> 00:15:40,845
It's true.

157
00:15:41,945 --> 00:15:43,345
So when knowledge matures,

158
00:15:43,885 --> 00:15:44,915
does it become wisdom?

159
00:15:47,385 --> 00:15:51,285
You may be half-joking with me,
but I only ever mean what I say.

160
00:15:51,655 --> 00:15:53,195
I don't joke around with just anyone.

161
00:15:57,525 --> 00:15:59,865
How about the Sky Hotel Lounge?

162
00:16:02,735 --> 00:16:03,735
Forget it.

163
00:16:06,575 --> 00:16:08,905
Is the Sky Hotel Lounge okay?

164
00:16:11,945 --> 00:16:13,575
So, is she ready to get married
as early as next month?

165
00:16:16,915 --> 00:16:18,315
That's up to you.

166
00:16:21,215 --> 00:16:22,615
How many cups of coffee
is that for you today?

167
00:16:23,825 --> 00:16:24,825
Four?

168
00:16:25,085 --> 00:16:26,085
That's enough.

169
00:16:27,455 --> 00:16:30,865
Drink something healthy and nutritious.
At least when you're with me.

170
00:16:32,525 --> 00:16:34,265
If this goes well, how about some Chalet?

171
00:16:35,195 --> 00:16:36,335
Is "Eruchal" the thing these days?

172
00:16:36,935 --> 00:16:39,035
I'll deck you out from head to toe.

173
00:16:39,565 --> 00:16:42,805
Clothes by Chalet, shoes by Rugati,
a bag by Evua.

174
00:16:45,605 --> 00:16:46,845
Or an all-Chalet look?

175
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:49,075
I don't want you to call me
anything different.

176
00:16:50,815 --> 00:16:52,215
Even when we get older,

177
00:16:52,645 --> 00:16:54,385
can't you just keep calling me
what you always have?

178
00:16:55,415 --> 00:16:57,085
I'll take that over all
the designer gifts.

179
00:16:59,255 --> 00:17:00,395
A long time ago,

180
00:17:01,725 --> 00:17:03,425
the first time we met,
in front of the supermarket.

181
00:17:04,525 --> 00:17:05,525
You mean, "Hey, kiddo?"

182
00:17:10,965 --> 00:17:12,565
You're the only person...

183
00:17:14,405 --> 00:17:16,005
who called me that way,

184
00:17:16,705 --> 00:17:17,775
as far as I can remember.

185
00:17:34,355 --> 00:17:35,395
Yong Joong.

186
00:17:39,495 --> 00:17:40,535
We...

187
00:17:41,365 --> 00:17:42,865
seem to really click.

188
00:17:45,465 --> 00:17:46,575
Am I sexy, too?

189
00:17:50,475 --> 00:17:52,475
Turns out, honesty can be sexy.

190
00:17:55,775 --> 00:17:57,315
And you are being
seriously sexy right now.

191
00:18:00,185 --> 00:18:01,315
(James)

192
00:18:05,325 --> 00:18:07,125
- Hey, James.
- Are you out?

193
00:18:07,195 --> 00:18:09,895
Yeah, at a local café with Ba Ra.
You're on speakerphone.

194
00:18:10,495 --> 00:18:11,695
Hey, Reporter Geum.

195
00:18:12,725 --> 00:18:15,935
- Hello.
- So what did my brother get you?

196
00:18:16,265 --> 00:18:17,505
What did he buy you?

197
00:18:17,605 --> 00:18:21,875
Not even a teddy bear this time.
He just said Korean stuff is better.

198
00:18:22,035 --> 00:18:26,375
- I'll get her a bag tomorrow. I'm broke.
- Make sure you get it.

199
00:18:27,045 --> 00:18:30,115
By the way, Reporter Geum,
have you spoken with Momo recently?

200
00:18:30,745 --> 00:18:34,255
- No.
- Is it possible she hasn't woken up yet?

201
00:18:34,515 --> 00:18:36,785
- Why?
- You didn't hear from Reporter Geum?

202
00:18:37,225 --> 00:18:41,425
Momo supposedly passed out scuba diving,
but now she's completely off the radar.

203
00:19:15,495 --> 00:19:16,495
You startled me.

204
00:19:24,135 --> 00:19:26,875
- Are you on a diet?
- I ate way too much yesterday.

205
00:19:32,345 --> 00:19:33,375
It's weird saying this, but...

206
00:19:34,145 --> 00:19:38,115
- Go on.
- I think you would've made a great woman.

207
00:19:38,885 --> 00:19:41,915
- A compliment on my cooking or an insult?
- A compliment.

208
00:19:42,415 --> 00:19:44,155
But there are way too many side dishes.

209
00:19:47,295 --> 00:19:49,295
I don't eat like this when I'm by myself.

210
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:52,325
You're really getting old.
You used to stuff your face late at night,

211
00:19:52,395 --> 00:19:55,335
and still grill meat at dawn.
Now that you're pushing 50...

212
00:19:58,435 --> 00:20:01,575
I'm a light sleeper.
Why didn't I hear your car pull up?

213
00:20:01,735 --> 00:20:04,375
Because you're old.
Your hearing is the next thing to go.

214
00:20:04,445 --> 00:20:07,545
- Your eyes are already going, too.
- You think you'll stay young forever?

215
00:20:07,645 --> 00:20:10,245
- No.
- You're really asking for it.

216
00:20:10,885 --> 00:20:12,815
I took a cab because I drank.

217
00:20:18,055 --> 00:20:19,825
Is something wrong at the company?

218
00:20:23,095 --> 00:20:24,525
Maybe something's wrong with Momo.

219
00:20:25,695 --> 00:20:27,365
Is that what's bothering you?

220
00:20:28,565 --> 00:20:30,305
Yesterday,
I just felt like having a drink.

221
00:20:31,565 --> 00:20:36,375
Forget Momo and focus on your own life.
I'm dying to hold a niece or nephew.

222
00:20:37,075 --> 00:20:38,405
That's my wish, too.

223
00:20:39,605 --> 00:20:41,375
Is it that hard for you to move on?

224
00:20:41,915 --> 00:20:43,075
Why wouldn't I be able to?

225
00:20:45,115 --> 00:20:46,885
It's just that I'm concerned, that's all.

226
00:20:47,515 --> 00:20:50,455
Why would you be concerned?
She's your best friend's fiancee.

227
00:20:50,755 --> 00:20:52,325
I wouldn't be
if they were happily married.

228
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:54,725
You think I've only known Ju Shin
for two years?

229
00:20:57,495 --> 00:20:59,195
And it feels like he's hiding something.

230
00:21:02,565 --> 00:21:05,105
I looked into it,
and her decompression sickness is severe.

231
00:21:05,265 --> 00:21:07,505
You can bet Director Shin is taking
the best possible care of her.

232
00:21:09,275 --> 00:21:11,445
Here, take a container of this kimchi
to Ba Ra.

233
00:21:11,905 --> 00:21:13,045
I don't know her address.

234
00:21:14,475 --> 00:21:15,745
You don't know her address?

235
00:21:34,365 --> 00:21:36,065
Burn it. I'm not taking it.

236
00:21:41,575 --> 00:21:43,605
(Nua General Hospital)

237
00:22:05,425 --> 00:22:07,765
Momo, get a grip.

238
00:22:08,365 --> 00:22:09,565
Walk like you're okay.

239
00:22:23,945 --> 00:22:25,015
(Republic of Korea passport)

240
00:22:42,995 --> 00:22:44,805
Director Shin, you know Geum Ba Ra, right?

241
00:22:45,705 --> 00:22:46,775
Yes.

242
00:22:46,875 --> 00:22:49,875
I think Ba Ra is digging around
for information on Momo.

243
00:22:50,005 --> 00:22:52,075
It looks like she even met with
the scuba instructor.

244
00:22:55,375 --> 00:22:58,745
I'm not writing an article, I promise.
You know me better than that, Manager Oh.

245
00:22:59,045 --> 00:23:01,055
CEO Hyun said she's doing perfectly fine.

246
00:23:01,255 --> 00:23:02,615
Have you seen her since the accident?

247
00:23:03,185 --> 00:23:04,855
- I haven't.
- Does that make sense?

248
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:06,795
She told me not to worry, so...

249
00:23:08,325 --> 00:23:11,325
- If you meet with CEO Hyun...
- I've already texted her,

250
00:23:12,165 --> 00:23:13,295
but I got no reply.

251
00:23:22,575 --> 00:23:23,575
So?

252
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:30,615
I just thought you should know
since it's about Momo.

253
00:23:37,025 --> 00:23:40,095
Doesn't it seem strange to you too?
With your reporter's intuition.

254
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:47,435
Like you say,

255
00:23:48,895 --> 00:23:50,535
what if Momo is in some kind of...

256
00:23:51,505 --> 00:23:53,105
worst-case scenario,

257
00:23:55,575 --> 00:23:56,805
what are you going to do then?

258
00:24:01,415 --> 00:24:02,545
When it comes to the heart...

259
00:24:05,115 --> 00:24:06,915
Shin Ju Shin has a cold side.

260
00:24:07,485 --> 00:24:09,115
To put it nicely, he's just rational.

261
00:24:10,755 --> 00:24:12,125
And it's not like they're married.

262
00:24:13,755 --> 00:24:16,295
In that situation, I wonder how long
he can keep looking after her.

263
00:24:17,695 --> 00:24:20,595
He's bound to get worn out.
And it's not like he has a low-stress job.

264
00:24:23,135 --> 00:24:24,505
And you wouldn't get worn out?

265
00:24:32,275 --> 00:24:33,515
Slow down.

266
00:24:43,455 --> 00:24:44,925
You've never really been in love,
have you?

267
00:24:48,095 --> 00:24:49,625
And for you, that's Momo?

268
00:24:54,395 --> 00:24:55,895
What's so great about her, anyway?

269
00:24:57,835 --> 00:24:58,935
Is it because she's a celebrity?

270
00:25:00,375 --> 00:25:02,475
Lee Ye Rim, Hong Mi Jeong,
and Jeong Chun Hee are celebrities, too.

271
00:25:02,635 --> 00:25:04,105
I've met them all at gatherings.

272
00:25:06,775 --> 00:25:07,875
You can't really explain...

273
00:25:09,515 --> 00:25:11,185
a person's feelings, you know?

274
00:25:14,315 --> 00:25:16,755
If the situation is really that serious,

275
00:25:18,225 --> 00:25:20,325
and Director Shin
eventually gives up on her...

276
00:25:23,565 --> 00:25:25,325
are you saying you're going to take
responsibility for her?

277
00:25:27,635 --> 00:25:28,635
For her entire life?

278
00:25:34,835 --> 00:25:36,375
How noble of you.

279
00:25:37,675 --> 00:25:40,175
To Mr. Ha and his undying love.

280
00:25:48,285 --> 00:25:49,885
You're not being yourself today.

281
00:25:50,485 --> 00:25:51,585
You're so cynical.

282
00:25:53,695 --> 00:25:55,155
How well do you even know me?

283
00:25:56,495 --> 00:25:59,195
What is it that I don't know? Tell me.

284
00:26:02,235 --> 00:26:05,765
Other than that I was an abandoned orphan,
you know nothing about me.

285
00:26:06,235 --> 00:26:07,605
You weren't abandoned.

286
00:26:08,505 --> 00:26:10,905
It must have been an impossible situation.
I can tell by looking at you.

287
00:26:11,975 --> 00:26:13,445
I can tell it's in your blood.

288
00:26:14,415 --> 00:26:15,575
You've got good character.

289
00:26:18,345 --> 00:26:19,445
My name...

290
00:26:21,385 --> 00:26:22,485
Who gave you that name?

291
00:26:25,225 --> 00:26:26,685
How would I know?

292
00:26:31,825 --> 00:26:33,065
But I think...

293
00:26:33,665 --> 00:26:34,935
It's just a guess...

294
00:26:38,535 --> 00:26:39,735
I'd rather not say.

295
00:26:46,745 --> 00:26:47,745
Are you mad at me?

296
00:26:50,385 --> 00:26:52,015
I thought you'd understand.

297
00:26:56,385 --> 00:26:59,985
I don't like how you're addressing me.
Don't call me Mr. Ha. It feels impersonal.

298
00:27:00,625 --> 00:27:02,225
It's not like we have that many employees.

299
00:27:03,725 --> 00:27:05,625
You should meet Director Shin,

300
00:27:06,295 --> 00:27:08,735
find a way to see Momo for yourself,

301
00:27:09,565 --> 00:27:11,305
and settle this once and for all.

302
00:27:21,575 --> 00:27:24,485
I have an article to write.
I'll get going.

303
00:27:25,315 --> 00:27:26,315
- Excuse me?
- Yes.

304
00:27:26,385 --> 00:27:27,415
No, go ahead and finish your drink.

305
00:27:39,195 --> 00:27:40,435
(Available)

306
00:29:17,025 --> 00:29:18,165
How's Momo?

307
00:29:20,795 --> 00:29:22,265
I don't want her to see me like this.

308
00:29:25,935 --> 00:29:27,035
She's the same.

309
00:29:33,545 --> 00:29:35,175
Don't let your mind run wild.

310
00:29:36,075 --> 00:29:37,785
I'll wrap this up without any issues.

311
00:29:40,015 --> 00:29:41,155
How are you going to wrap it up?

312
00:29:44,025 --> 00:29:46,025
How did your seminar presentation go?

313
00:29:47,155 --> 00:29:48,155
It was fine.

314
00:29:49,595 --> 00:29:52,495
- I'm sorry. I came empty-handed.
- Don't be silly.

315
00:29:55,435 --> 00:29:56,635
This is all very confusing, isn't it?

316
00:29:57,235 --> 00:29:58,765
You'll get used to it. Eventually.

317
00:30:01,305 --> 00:30:03,405
You should go. You must be tired.

318
00:30:28,935 --> 00:30:30,565
Sometimes when I look in the mirror,

319
00:30:31,265 --> 00:30:34,835
I can't tell if I'm Momo
or if I'm looking at her.

320
00:31:36,465 --> 00:31:41,835
(Yong Joong)

321
00:32:06,965 --> 00:32:07,995
Momo...

322
00:32:11,805 --> 00:32:13,565
How can I live without seeing her?

323
00:32:34,855 --> 00:32:36,455
(Ba Ra)

324
00:32:36,825 --> 00:32:38,365
(Send me your address...)

325
00:32:45,565 --> 00:32:47,275
(Send me your address...)

326
00:32:47,335 --> 00:32:48,335
(Where do you live? Are you asleep?)

327
00:33:10,195 --> 00:33:11,395
(Yong Joong)

328
00:33:11,625 --> 00:33:12,965
Are you still mad, kiddo?

329
00:33:33,645 --> 00:33:34,655
What book is that?

330
00:33:35,255 --> 00:33:37,355
("Mouth Management")

331
00:33:39,855 --> 00:33:40,855
Come on up.

332
00:33:42,355 --> 00:33:46,225
- Is this a bad time?
- I can't eat out. I have surgery later.

333
00:34:00,375 --> 00:34:04,815
We were all in disbelief
when your father passed so suddenly.

334
00:34:04,885 --> 00:34:07,755
- Were you there?
- As the orphanage's representative.

335
00:34:08,685 --> 00:34:10,415
So many people came to pay their respects.

336
00:34:11,785 --> 00:34:15,325
Honestly, my mother's death was harder.
I was just a kid.

337
00:34:17,025 --> 00:34:18,025
Am I making you uncomfortable?

338
00:34:18,665 --> 00:34:21,365
Do you mind if I get this to go?
I usually have late lunch.

339
00:34:21,635 --> 00:34:22,735
This is my first meal of the day.

340
00:34:24,965 --> 00:34:26,665
Are you going around investigating Momo?

341
00:34:27,875 --> 00:34:30,135
- I heard about it.
- From who?

342
00:34:35,745 --> 00:34:38,145
- It's not an investigation. It's...
- For a story?

343
00:34:38,645 --> 00:34:39,745
Or as a concerned friend?

344
00:34:43,655 --> 00:34:45,355
I heard you two were pretty close.

345
00:34:48,825 --> 00:34:52,495
I'm just worried.
I haven't heard from her in so long.

346
00:34:52,795 --> 00:34:55,595
Her phone is still turned off,
and Jin Ju said she had an accident...

347
00:34:55,665 --> 00:34:56,935
It wasn't that serious an accident.

348
00:34:58,305 --> 00:34:59,705
She's out of the country.

349
00:35:00,605 --> 00:35:02,435
She was exhausted,
so I told her to take a break.

350
00:35:05,005 --> 00:35:06,275
She'll be back soon enough.

351
00:35:07,375 --> 00:35:09,115
About me and Momo dating...

352
00:35:10,345 --> 00:35:11,485
Did you hear it from Kim Jin Ju?

353
00:35:13,615 --> 00:35:17,185
I can't reveal my sources.
It wasn't Jin Ju.

354
00:35:17,255 --> 00:35:21,295
We're both too busy to see each other.
We just run into each other at gatherings.

355
00:35:21,355 --> 00:35:22,855
And even that was only once in a while.

356
00:35:22,925 --> 00:35:25,225
You know my father was very proud of you,
don't you?

357
00:35:28,995 --> 00:35:30,365
Running the foundation...

358
00:35:31,165 --> 00:35:32,465
He found it so worthwhile.

359
00:35:35,835 --> 00:35:37,975
If you ever need help with anything,
let me know.

360
00:35:38,645 --> 00:35:40,945
- I don't.
- You never know.

361
00:35:41,575 --> 00:35:42,745
Don't be so sure.

362
00:35:44,745 --> 00:35:47,515
By the way,
I saw you interviewed Ha Yong Joong.

363
00:35:47,955 --> 00:35:49,185
He's been a friend of mine
since we were kids.

364
00:35:50,115 --> 00:35:52,825
He also played the double bass
at the appreciation gala.

365
00:35:52,885 --> 00:35:54,595
Why did you leave so early that night?

366
00:35:55,595 --> 00:35:57,795
I was running a little late
because I had an emergency surgery,

367
00:35:58,965 --> 00:35:59,965
and I saw you were leaving.

368
00:36:01,035 --> 00:36:02,635
I remember because of your ivory coat.

369
00:36:03,465 --> 00:36:05,665
My mother used to wear an ivory coat
a lot.

370
00:36:08,735 --> 00:36:10,575
Please tell Momo I said hi.

371
00:36:15,445 --> 00:36:16,675
I'll take it to go.

372
00:36:21,515 --> 00:36:24,155
Pack it for her to go. The sandwiches.

373
00:36:32,695 --> 00:36:35,695
I can't relay the message.
You should tell her in person.

374
00:36:43,505 --> 00:36:44,505
Hello?

375
00:36:45,405 --> 00:36:47,975
- Yes?
- Where've you been? Haven't you seen it?

376
00:36:48,045 --> 00:36:50,645
- The article on Momo's engagement.
- Where did it run?

377
00:36:51,385 --> 00:36:52,415
Got it.

378
00:36:55,655 --> 00:36:57,685
The inevitable has happened, Momo.

379
00:36:58,055 --> 00:36:59,825
Did you already know about this, sir?

380
00:37:05,225 --> 00:37:06,795
("Exclusive, Momo's Secret Engagement!")

381
00:37:06,795 --> 00:37:07,935
("Fiance is Director Shin Ju Shin
of Nua Medical")

382
00:37:16,135 --> 00:37:18,205
("Exclusive, Momo's Secret Engagement!")

383
00:37:18,205 --> 00:37:19,575
(Two families have met.
Yet, there is no official announcement.)

384
00:37:22,845 --> 00:37:24,485
(Surprised by his handsome looks,
belying his director title...)

385
00:37:24,545 --> 00:37:25,545
(Innocent looks that belie his title...)

386
00:37:25,615 --> 00:37:27,345
(and even more surprised
by his fresh-faced youth)

387
00:37:27,415 --> 00:37:30,615
(We interviewed Director Shin and heard
the full story of their romance.)

388
00:37:35,095 --> 00:37:36,625
- Is this for real?
- We need to publish by eight o'clock.

389
00:37:37,495 --> 00:37:39,665
- Hey, over there.
- This is it.

390
00:37:45,765 --> 00:37:48,105
("Exclusive Interview with Momo's Fiance,
Director Shin Ju Shin")

391
00:37:48,775 --> 00:37:51,475
I just met with Director Shin Ju Shin
and posted the interview.

392
00:37:51,845 --> 00:37:52,845
You interviewed him?

393
00:37:53,145 --> 00:37:54,915
- Yes.
- When?

394
00:37:54,975 --> 00:37:58,485
- I was with him when you called earlier.
- You should've told me then!

395
00:37:59,085 --> 00:38:00,085
I knew you'd pull through.

396
00:38:11,095 --> 00:38:12,095
Yes?

397
00:38:12,825 --> 00:38:14,535
I just met with Director Shin Ju Shin.

398
00:38:15,165 --> 00:38:17,835
He said Momo's fine
and that she's gone abroad to rest.

399
00:38:19,535 --> 00:38:20,535
That's a relief.

400
00:38:23,575 --> 00:38:24,645
Did you see the article?

401
00:38:25,945 --> 00:38:26,945
Yes.

402
00:38:30,315 --> 00:38:34,045
Can you toss me a decent engagement photo?
You must've taken some, right?

403
00:38:34,355 --> 00:38:35,615
A really nice one of the two of them.

404
00:38:37,255 --> 00:38:38,355
Ju Shin would kill me.

405
00:38:38,725 --> 00:38:40,895
His picture's already out there
and the story went viral.

406
00:38:41,725 --> 00:38:43,555
Do you have any idea
how much my boss chewed me out?

407
00:38:44,055 --> 00:38:45,925
All because I was trying to be loyal
and keep it a secret...

408
00:38:48,995 --> 00:38:50,935
I won't reveal my source, of course.

409
00:38:51,435 --> 00:38:54,065
People will just assume
it was leaked by the wedding studio.

410
00:38:54,535 --> 00:38:56,635
- If I can't make up for this...
- All right, fine.

411
00:38:58,675 --> 00:38:59,705
What's with the sudden change of heart?

412
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:01,845
You've been ignoring
all my calls and texts.

413
00:39:04,885 --> 00:39:05,945
It's not a change of heart.

414
00:39:07,115 --> 00:39:08,115
Then what is it?

415
00:39:09,855 --> 00:39:10,855
I'm sorry.

416
00:39:11,355 --> 00:39:12,685
I'll be more respectful from now on.

417
00:39:15,125 --> 00:39:17,325
- Director Shin Ju Shin!
- Just give us one comment!

418
00:39:17,395 --> 00:39:18,995
- I have an interview with Mr. Shin!
- He has patients to see.

419
00:39:19,065 --> 00:39:21,965
- We're reporting from Momo's house.
- Please just open the door!

420
00:39:22,065 --> 00:39:23,435
- We're from CBS News!
- Come on, please open the door!

421
00:39:23,495 --> 00:39:25,635
- Please, just open the door!
- Just open up!

422
00:39:25,705 --> 00:39:26,705
This will only take a moment!

423
00:39:40,885 --> 00:39:41,885
What are you doing?

424
00:39:44,055 --> 00:39:45,055
Go back inside.

425
00:39:48,655 --> 00:39:49,655
Who am I?

426
00:39:53,295 --> 00:39:54,565
I...

427
00:39:55,995 --> 00:39:58,405
The one you're referring to...
Who is that?

428
00:40:04,545 --> 00:40:05,875
Don't you miss me?

429
00:40:07,075 --> 00:40:08,215
You don't remember me?

430
00:40:11,485 --> 00:40:12,645
I don't know.

431
00:40:17,315 --> 00:40:18,625
Get lost.

432
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:20,625
You get lost.

433
00:40:23,825 --> 00:40:25,265
You're so dead.

434
00:40:26,125 --> 00:40:27,295
How can you say that to me, your mom?

435
00:40:29,835 --> 00:40:30,965
(Surgery Center)

436
00:40:31,665 --> 00:40:32,665
What am I going to do?

437
00:40:33,205 --> 00:40:35,405
They won't stop ringing the bell,
so I had to turn off the intercom.

438
00:40:36,035 --> 00:40:37,305
For now, there's no other way...

439
00:40:39,245 --> 00:40:40,245
but to endure it.

440
00:40:40,775 --> 00:40:42,945
So we endure it, and then what?

441
00:40:45,515 --> 00:40:46,515
They broke up?

442
00:40:46,785 --> 00:40:47,815
I'll think about it.

443
00:40:50,285 --> 00:40:51,285
Let me think about it.

444
00:40:53,055 --> 00:40:54,125
I guess you have no other choice.

445
00:40:59,665 --> 00:41:01,025
Then just announce it tomorrow.

446
00:41:01,665 --> 00:41:02,795
I won't have any time for a while.

447
00:41:03,995 --> 00:41:05,335
And that'll just stir up
another huge mess.

448
00:41:05,505 --> 00:41:07,665
If you're so busy, why'd you
even do that interview with Sungwoo Daily?

449
00:41:08,035 --> 00:41:09,035
I didn't give them an interview.

450
00:41:09,735 --> 00:41:10,775
She's a reporter, all right.

451
00:41:12,645 --> 00:41:14,415
I heard she was snooping around
like she was onto something.

452
00:41:14,775 --> 00:41:16,115
So I called her in
and gave her the runaround, but...

453
00:41:16,475 --> 00:41:17,515
And that's what she wrote?

454
00:41:18,015 --> 00:41:19,015
Yes.

455
00:41:20,585 --> 00:41:23,415
Hello. We met before
at the exhibit with Momo.

456
00:41:23,955 --> 00:41:25,185
I'm from the culture desk
at Sungwoo Daily.

457
00:41:27,085 --> 00:41:28,795
I could tell she was something else.

458
00:41:29,895 --> 00:41:30,955
(Sungwoo Daily)

459
00:41:32,425 --> 00:41:34,265
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

460
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:40,535
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

461
00:41:42,135 --> 00:41:43,135
Yes, Director Shin.

462
00:41:43,775 --> 00:41:45,245
Did I have an interview with you today?

463
00:41:47,105 --> 00:41:48,115
I'm sorry.

464
00:41:48,815 --> 00:41:51,645
I'm in the middle of writing the article.
Can I call you back when I'm done?

465
00:41:51,985 --> 00:41:52,985
Another story about us?

466
00:41:53,585 --> 00:41:55,355
Yes, a follow-up piece.

467
00:41:55,955 --> 00:41:56,955
Geum Ba Ra.

468
00:41:57,355 --> 00:41:58,355
Yes, Director Shin.

469
00:41:59,825 --> 00:42:00,985
You're biting the hand that fed you?

470
00:42:02,155 --> 00:42:04,625
And you, of all people,
are going to take it even further?

471
00:42:05,365 --> 00:42:07,595
- After you read the article...
- Don't write anything else.

472
00:42:10,565 --> 00:42:13,465
Rather than let other outlets
write sensationalist garbage,

473
00:42:13,905 --> 00:42:15,805
it's better to release
a well-written story based on the facts...

474
00:42:15,875 --> 00:42:18,805
and help both of your images.
That is my professional opinion.

475
00:42:19,045 --> 00:42:20,205
And who are you to make that call?

476
00:42:21,105 --> 00:42:23,415
An interview that never happened.
That's what's fiction, an outright lie.

477
00:42:24,045 --> 00:42:25,385
I'll make sure you have nothing
to worry about.

478
00:42:25,445 --> 00:42:27,645
Is that what they taught you
at the Nua Orphanage?

479
00:42:28,115 --> 00:42:29,485
I wasn't taught anything there.

480
00:42:29,915 --> 00:42:33,225
You should have a shred of conscience.
You'll stop at nothing...

481
00:42:33,285 --> 00:42:34,895
I'll call you when I'm finished.

482
00:42:36,155 --> 00:42:37,155
Goodbye.

483
00:42:46,335 --> 00:42:47,935
("Rumors of Momo's Broken Engagement,
Couple Not in Contact")

484
00:42:48,005 --> 00:42:49,935
("Momo's Representative on Rumors:
'No Comment,' A Puzzling Response")

485
00:42:50,005 --> 00:42:51,275
("Scoop:
Momo's Fairytale-like Secret Engagement")

486
00:42:53,045 --> 00:42:54,345
("Scoop:
Momo's Fairytale-like Secret Engagement")

487
00:42:54,775 --> 00:42:56,575
("Momo's Fairytale-like
Secret Engagement")

488
00:42:58,745 --> 00:43:00,545
("Momo's Fairytale-like
Secret Engagement")

489
00:43:00,615 --> 00:43:04,055
(Geum Ba Ra)

490
00:43:08,395 --> 00:43:09,395
Hello?

491
00:43:10,625 --> 00:43:11,625
This is Geum Ba Ra.

492
00:43:12,095 --> 00:43:13,795
Because of this exclusive interview
that never happened,

493
00:43:14,965 --> 00:43:16,465
all the other news outlets
are in an uproar.

494
00:43:17,365 --> 00:43:19,965
May I state my opinion?

495
00:43:22,735 --> 00:43:24,845
At the end of the day,
it's true that you two are engaged.

496
00:43:24,905 --> 00:43:26,945
It's a reporter's calling
to report the truth.

497
00:43:28,545 --> 00:43:29,945
I'm asking why you published
a fabricated story.

498
00:43:31,445 --> 00:43:33,685
What did Momo say?

499
00:43:36,155 --> 00:43:37,925
Just answer my question.

500
00:43:38,555 --> 00:43:39,985
As you said,

501
00:43:40,355 --> 00:43:42,895
When the Chairman treated me to dinner
after I got into college,

502
00:43:43,455 --> 00:43:46,865
he told me I was the face
and the pride of Nua Orphanage.

503
00:43:47,495 --> 00:43:50,035
Everyone at my company knows
I grew up in an orphanage,

504
00:43:50,465 --> 00:43:52,835
so I have to work harder than the others
just so they won't dismiss me.

505
00:43:52,905 --> 00:43:54,935
That's how I survive in this business
without getting crushed.

506
00:43:55,575 --> 00:43:57,075
If I succeed and make a name for myself,

507
00:43:57,875 --> 00:44:00,775
you think you'll never need a favor
from me, Director Shin?

508
00:44:01,645 --> 00:44:03,015
You think I don't have connections
in the media?

509
00:44:04,885 --> 00:44:05,915
I've more than I know what to do with.

510
00:44:06,845 --> 00:44:10,515
I'm sure you do.
But I'm not just a typical connection.

511
00:44:11,285 --> 00:44:13,425
When you get down to it,
you could call me family.

512
00:44:13,985 --> 00:44:15,525
Part of the Nua Foundation family.

513
00:44:18,865 --> 00:44:21,965
Please, just think of it
as giving me a leg up.

514
00:44:23,265 --> 00:44:24,735
You have every right to be upset.

515
00:44:26,335 --> 00:44:27,665
And for that, I apologize.

516
00:44:29,475 --> 00:44:32,445
To be honest,
I knew about your engagement for a while.

517
00:44:34,045 --> 00:44:35,175
You heard it from Kim Jin Ju, didn't you?

518
00:44:36,245 --> 00:44:38,945
I'm on the Culture Desk, so I have sources
at the salons that celebrities frequent.

519
00:44:39,015 --> 00:44:41,585
I get all kinds of intel from them.
It's fast and accurate.

520
00:44:45,155 --> 00:44:46,155
I'll let it slide this time.

521
00:44:46,725 --> 00:44:47,955
Don't you dare stab me in the back again.

522
00:44:49,355 --> 00:44:50,355
I promise.

523
00:44:52,025 --> 00:44:53,395
You owe me one.

524
00:44:54,995 --> 00:44:58,505
I wouldn't be where I am today
without the Chairman and you, Director.

525
00:44:59,165 --> 00:45:01,035
I will be sure to repay everything I owe,
including this.

526
00:45:01,505 --> 00:45:03,505
I don't care if you're a reporter
or the head of a media company,

527
00:45:04,675 --> 00:45:06,045
You do not cross the line with me.

528
00:45:07,775 --> 00:45:09,845
Yes. I'm sorry.

529
00:45:10,515 --> 00:45:11,515
You can go now.

530
00:45:11,885 --> 00:45:12,885
Yes, sir.

531
00:45:53,125 --> 00:45:54,555
Is there anything you want to eat?

532
00:45:58,995 --> 00:46:00,065
Who am I?

533
00:46:24,655 --> 00:46:25,955
(To my dearest Momo,)

534
00:46:26,025 --> 00:46:27,255
My dearest Momo.

535
00:46:28,755 --> 00:46:29,825
If it weren't for you,

536
00:46:31,465 --> 00:46:34,495
I would've left this world
a long time ago.

537
00:46:36,035 --> 00:46:37,535
That I have to leave you like this...

538
00:46:50,015 --> 00:46:51,615
this mother who is leaving you now...

539
00:46:52,385 --> 00:46:54,185
I hope you can understand and forgive me.

540
00:46:56,585 --> 00:46:58,385
I could never let you see,

541
00:46:59,455 --> 00:47:00,725
but at some point,

542
00:47:01,455 --> 00:47:05,825
I find it hard to even breathe.

543
00:47:08,025 --> 00:47:09,195
For no reason at all,

544
00:47:10,235 --> 00:47:11,805
every day was filled with despair...

545
00:47:12,565 --> 00:47:13,865
and sorrow.

546
00:47:15,735 --> 00:47:17,435
I tried to hold on a little longer,

547
00:47:19,105 --> 00:47:20,975
but in place of this weak,
pathetic mother,

548
00:47:23,015 --> 00:47:24,045
you have Director Shin,
someone who cherishes you...

549
00:47:25,285 --> 00:47:27,615
and loves you so dearly.

550
00:47:28,685 --> 00:47:29,855
I can leave now, because I trust him.

551
00:47:32,685 --> 00:47:34,425
Please, let me go without any tears.

552
00:47:37,555 --> 00:47:38,565
I feel deeply sorry...

553
00:47:39,495 --> 00:47:41,765
to Dr. Jung,

554
00:47:42,265 --> 00:47:45,205
who tried everything...

555
00:47:46,035 --> 00:47:47,065
to cure the sickness in my soul.

556
00:47:49,135 --> 00:47:50,575
To my many acquaintances,

557
00:47:52,345 --> 00:47:54,645
I can see all their faces now.

558
00:47:56,845 --> 00:47:59,715
My dear daughter,
don't be foolish like me...

559
00:48:00,115 --> 00:48:02,285
and don't bury yourself in your work.

560
00:48:03,715 --> 00:48:07,685
From now on, learn to enjoy life a little,

561
00:48:08,995 --> 00:48:10,895
and always try to keep your spirits up.

562
00:48:15,395 --> 00:48:19,905
Please, live a long and healthy life.
Live well, for my sake too.

563
00:48:22,275 --> 00:48:25,145
The good deeds I wasn't able to finish...

564
00:48:26,975 --> 00:48:28,975
Do plenty of them with Director Shin.

565
00:48:30,915 --> 00:48:32,615
I don't want to be buried
in the cold, dark ground.

566
00:48:35,215 --> 00:48:36,215
Please have me cremated.

567
00:48:39,185 --> 00:48:41,425
I love you, my daughter.

568
00:48:44,225 --> 00:48:49,665
(Paul Kim)

569
00:48:54,105 --> 00:48:57,035
(Incoming Call)

570
00:49:01,205 --> 00:49:02,215
This is Paul Kim.

571
00:49:02,845 --> 00:49:07,115
Hi, I'm calling about the painting
you sold to CEO James Ha of Lim Company.

572
00:49:08,785 --> 00:49:09,785
Yes.

573
00:49:10,285 --> 00:49:11,755
I'm an acquaintance of CEO Ha's.

574
00:49:12,485 --> 00:49:15,195
I found the mood of that painting
so unique and refreshing.

575
00:49:15,995 --> 00:49:17,825
I assume you have other pieces
at your studio?

576
00:49:18,925 --> 00:49:22,635
- I do.
- I'd like to purchase one. May I stop by?

577
00:49:22,935 --> 00:49:24,735
My studio is on the outskirts of Seoul.

578
00:49:25,035 --> 00:49:27,305
That's fine.
It's only one hour at most with traffic.

579
00:49:27,705 --> 00:49:28,705
Do you have the address?

580
00:49:29,975 --> 00:49:31,075
Could you give it to me?

581
00:49:50,655 --> 00:49:51,725
It's open. Come on in.

582
00:50:11,045 --> 00:50:13,115
Paul Kim?

583
00:50:14,815 --> 00:50:15,815
Yes.

584
00:50:16,655 --> 00:50:18,825
Hello. Sorry I'm a bit late.

585
00:50:20,255 --> 00:50:23,495
The drive up here is just beautiful.

586
00:50:24,525 --> 00:50:25,525
Please, have a seat.

587
00:50:37,105 --> 00:50:39,275
You don't have any of your work
on display?

588
00:50:39,975 --> 00:50:40,975
No, I don't.

589
00:50:41,405 --> 00:50:42,875
They're in my studio
and on the second floor.

590
00:50:45,285 --> 00:50:47,515
- All I have is coffee.
- Coffee is perfect.

591
00:50:48,245 --> 00:50:49,785
No espresso, I presume?

592
00:50:53,025 --> 00:50:54,025
I'm just kidding.

593
00:50:59,265 --> 00:51:00,925
He surely is an artist.

594
00:51:01,765 --> 00:51:03,395
He's middle-aged,
but not an ounce of fat on him.

595
00:51:41,665 --> 00:51:42,675
This is delicious.

596
00:51:43,835 --> 00:51:44,835
It's German coffee.

597
00:51:45,575 --> 00:51:47,605
I heard you were based in Germany.

598
00:51:48,345 --> 00:51:49,345
Yes.

599
00:51:50,545 --> 00:51:53,585
I wasn't sure what to get you,
so I came empty-handed.

600
00:51:58,285 --> 00:51:59,285
You really didn't have to.

601
00:51:59,955 --> 00:52:00,955
There's nothing I need.

602
00:52:01,795 --> 00:52:02,925
I just meant some basic necessities.

603
00:52:05,025 --> 00:52:07,825
He's so stoic, like a Zen monk.

604
00:52:15,405 --> 00:52:16,405
I'm Hyun Ran Hee, by the way.

605
00:52:20,075 --> 00:52:21,775
(CEO Hyun Ran Hee)

606
00:52:24,045 --> 00:52:25,545
He must have heard of me.

607
00:52:28,315 --> 00:52:29,815
Do you do photography as well?

608
00:52:31,455 --> 00:52:32,455
Sometimes.

609
00:52:33,085 --> 00:52:34,725
So you must go out on photo shoots.

610
00:52:35,425 --> 00:52:37,125
When I have a block or feel drained.

611
00:52:37,725 --> 00:52:40,925
There's hardly any information
on you out there.

612
00:52:42,095 --> 00:52:43,595
When did you return to Korea?

613
00:52:44,565 --> 00:52:45,935
Seven months ago.

614
00:52:47,935 --> 00:52:50,805
So you knew CEO Ju before that?

615
00:52:51,405 --> 00:52:53,145
Yes, back in Germany.

616
00:52:54,845 --> 00:52:56,245
So CEO Ju sought you out?

617
00:52:56,715 --> 00:52:57,715
Yes.

618
00:52:58,045 --> 00:53:00,615
After seeing my work
at the Hong Kong Art Fair.

619
00:53:01,115 --> 00:53:02,885
The Hong Kong Art Fair? When was that?

620
00:53:03,515 --> 00:53:04,515
That was two years ago.

621
00:53:05,455 --> 00:53:08,255
I missed that one.

622
00:53:10,455 --> 00:53:12,065
No wedding ring, either.

623
00:53:26,345 --> 00:53:27,345
By any chance,

624
00:53:28,005 --> 00:53:30,175
is this a painting of someone
in your family?

625
00:53:31,475 --> 00:53:32,485
Your wife?

626
00:53:34,545 --> 00:53:36,655
It's just that the feeling
I get from it...

627
00:53:37,815 --> 00:53:38,885
is so profound.

628
00:53:40,785 --> 00:53:41,785
I don't have any family.

629
00:53:43,325 --> 00:53:45,725
Single? How attractive.

630
00:53:47,895 --> 00:53:50,995
When did you start focusing on people
as your subject?

631
00:53:52,535 --> 00:53:53,635
It's been a while.

632
00:53:54,765 --> 00:53:58,505
Clients love it.
These heartfelt paintings.

633
00:54:00,805 --> 00:54:02,145
This place is perfect for a studio.

634
00:54:02,745 --> 00:54:04,375
So, are you back for good?

635
00:54:05,185 --> 00:54:06,185
I am.

636
00:54:06,445 --> 00:54:09,555
Why don't I plan a solo exhibition
for you?

637
00:54:10,615 --> 00:54:11,715
Is it because of CEO Ju?

638
00:54:13,355 --> 00:54:14,555
Mother's Gallery?

639
00:54:15,355 --> 00:54:16,355
We're in talks.

640
00:54:18,295 --> 00:54:20,425
I'll take this with me today.

641
00:54:22,295 --> 00:54:23,535
She hasn't changed a bit.

642
00:54:32,975 --> 00:54:35,075
(Paul Kim)

643
00:54:41,515 --> 00:54:42,615
(Paul Kim)

644
00:54:42,755 --> 00:54:43,785
If you find her,

645
00:54:44,515 --> 00:54:46,585
tell her...

646
00:54:47,185 --> 00:54:48,185
that her mom was so, so sorry.

647
00:54:48,995 --> 00:54:51,355
You have to find her. No matter what.

648
00:55:38,645 --> 00:55:39,845
(One Missed Call, Ran Hee)

649
00:55:43,945 --> 00:55:45,015
If you find her,

650
00:55:45,685 --> 00:55:47,915
tell her...

651
00:55:48,415 --> 00:55:49,415
that her mom was so, so sorry.

652
00:55:50,215 --> 00:55:52,625
You have to find her. No matter what.

653
00:55:52,755 --> 00:55:54,855
(Ran Hee)

654
00:55:58,025 --> 00:56:01,795
The person you have called is unavailable.
Please leave a message after the tone.

655
00:56:09,175 --> 00:56:10,205
Hyun Ran Hee.

656
00:56:10,975 --> 00:56:12,405
You've worked so hard.

657
00:56:15,645 --> 00:56:17,015
And you're still so young.

658
00:56:17,745 --> 00:56:19,215
Still in your prime.

659
00:56:21,115 --> 00:56:22,585
That girl just wouldn't listen.

660
00:56:23,285 --> 00:56:25,385
I warned her over and over
that it was dangerous.

661
00:56:26,085 --> 00:56:27,085
Is this my karma?

662
00:56:28,385 --> 00:56:29,825
Even if it is, it can't be helped.

663
00:58:37,055 --> 00:58:38,515
Hello, is this the Immigration Office?

664
00:58:39,125 --> 00:58:41,955
I'm calling to check if an acquaintance
of mine has left the country.

665
00:58:42,025 --> 00:58:44,055
I can't let you know
as it's personal information.

666
00:58:44,055 --> 00:58:45,595
Not even if I come to the office?

667
00:58:45,695 --> 00:58:46,695
It wouldn't make a difference.

668
00:58:48,095 --> 00:58:49,095
I see.

669
00:58:55,575 --> 00:58:57,005
It's 911. What's your emergency?

670
00:58:57,405 --> 00:59:00,745
- I...
- Please state your emergency.

671
00:59:01,045 --> 00:59:04,415
Hurry. Please come quick. It's my mom...

672
00:59:04,845 --> 00:59:08,615
We had a few calls.
Mr. Oh Young Sik woke up in distress.

673
00:59:08,745 --> 00:59:11,785
He's intubated,
so he couldn't express himself clearly.

674
00:59:12,015 --> 00:59:16,325
Remifentanil didn't work.
So we used Propofol, and he settled down.

675
00:59:16,655 --> 00:59:20,965
When we started Precedex for sedation,
his blood pressure dropped slightly...

676
00:59:21,295 --> 00:59:23,665
(Conference Room)

677
00:59:23,835 --> 00:59:24,835
Hello?

678
00:59:27,235 --> 00:59:32,105
(Nua General Hospital ICU gets top rating
in quality assessment!)

679
00:59:32,475 --> 00:59:36,975
We can run a check,
but it's logged in the immigration system.

680
00:59:37,715 --> 00:59:38,715
Who is it?

681
00:59:39,915 --> 00:59:41,785
- A celebrity.
- Which one?

682
00:59:42,485 --> 00:59:45,015
I'll tell you,
but you have to stick your neck out.

683
00:59:45,085 --> 00:59:47,325
If I stick my neck out and lose my job,
are you going to take responsibility?

684
00:59:47,385 --> 00:59:50,855
- You won't be fired for this.
- Get forensics to Momo's house, now!

685
00:59:53,625 --> 00:59:56,435
What's going on at Momo's?
What happened? An accident?

686
00:59:58,095 --> 01:00:00,235
Don't you know me?
You're the one who called me a pit bull.

687
01:00:02,375 --> 01:00:04,505
It looks like Momo's mother
committed suicide.

688
01:00:04,935 --> 01:00:06,075
We still have to investigate, though.

689
01:00:06,445 --> 01:00:08,375
- Why?
- How would I know?

690
01:00:09,015 --> 01:00:10,015
What about Momo?

691
01:00:10,515 --> 01:00:12,075
Apparently, she's the one who called 911.

692
01:00:13,785 --> 01:00:14,985
(Forensics)

693
01:00:19,525 --> 01:00:21,255
(Sungwoo Daily)

694
01:00:25,225 --> 01:00:26,225
(Headline)

695
01:00:26,295 --> 01:00:27,895
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

696
01:00:29,435 --> 01:00:30,565
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

697
01:00:30,565 --> 01:00:31,665
("Momo Called 911")

698
01:00:32,635 --> 01:00:34,905
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

699
01:00:35,105 --> 01:00:37,005
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

700
01:00:40,305 --> 01:00:42,575
(Momo discovered the body and called 911.)

701
01:00:42,645 --> 01:00:44,745
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

702
01:00:47,015 --> 01:00:48,845
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

703
01:01:15,875 --> 01:01:18,715
(Doctor Shin)

704
01:01:18,845 --> 01:01:20,515
No way. This can't be happening. How?

705
01:01:21,085 --> 01:01:23,555
- What is it, sir?
- She's relentless.

706
01:01:25,515 --> 01:01:26,525
Momo...

707
01:01:28,225 --> 01:01:30,125
James, doesn't your company sponsor Momo?

708
01:01:30,825 --> 01:01:32,395
- Yes.
- Can you introduce me?

709
01:01:32,465 --> 01:01:35,465
I didn't realize you were his best friend.
I made a complete fool of myself.

710
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:37,565
- I'm Ha Yong Joong.
- I'm Momo.

711
01:01:37,635 --> 01:01:40,865
I can't believe it.
She got all that work done on her face,

712
01:01:41,005 --> 01:01:43,975
- and she looked so happy.
- Hyun Ran Hee is the one who died.

713
01:01:44,475 --> 01:01:46,075
Things are not what they seem.

714
01:01:46,705 --> 01:01:50,315
Just take it for what it is.
No need to overthink it.

715
01:01:50,875 --> 01:01:51,915
Loosen your tie before you go.

716
01:01:52,445 --> 01:01:55,855
I wonder where my daughter is
and if she's growing up well.

717
01:01:56,285 --> 01:01:59,955
He was the one who saw the good in me
when I felt worthless.

718
01:02:00,685 --> 01:02:04,095
- Yong Joong.
- They didn't even do CPR.

719
01:02:04,655 --> 01:02:06,095
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
